        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/sewbacca/{size}/49959_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-15T05:59:12.471Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I’d really like to be able to share screens bidirectionally with a friend, as currently it requires the other person to quit their stream in order to show your screen. It also makes tech support difficult as <em><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/u/pickle_umbrella\">@pickel_umbrella</a></em> pointed out earlier. (see below)</p>\n<h4><a name=\"p-257283-related-post-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-257283-related-post-1\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Related post</h4>\n<p>Searching the forum, I found post <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/screen-sharing-improvements/62112\">62112</a>, which included this request among many other requests. For better tracking I pulled their statement out here:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>2. Allow multiple users to share their screen at once.</strong> I’m not sure if this is a bug or if this just isn’t supported for some reason, but I was unable to share my screen while my friend was already sharing his screen. I tested again with my other friend and we still could not both share our screens. I don’t understand why we can both share our cameras but not our screens. This makes tech support very difficult as I was guiding my friend through a problem he was having, but I could not see his screen since only one of us could share it at a time. Because of this issue, we eventually hung up on Signal and called on Discord instead.<br>\n<em>~ <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/u/pickle_umbrella\">pickle_umbrella</a></em></p>\n</blockquote>",
