        "id": 282353,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Sewbacca",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/sewbacca/{size}/49959_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-07T18:20:10.351Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yet another workaround we found that requires skill:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create a <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/7860719423002-How-to-create-and-share-call-links\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">call link</a> for signal</li>\n<li>One joins the call and starts their screen cast</li>\n<li>Then the other one joins the call. Theres a brief window of 0.5 to 1 seconds where the screen share button is not disabled.</li>\n<li>If you are fast enough you can hit it before it get’s disabled, then you can start a bidirectional screen share. If not, log out of the call and join and try again.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So basically Signal could do bidirectional screen share all along, it’s just prohibited by the UI.<br>\nTested between Windows and Linux.</p>",
