        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/sewbacca/{size}/49959_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-19T15:07:52.715Z",
        "cooked": "<p>We found a more relaxing workaround: Simply go into the screen selection menu (hit the button), wait until the other person has shared their stream and only then start yours (by finishing the screen/window selection). No timing is necessary except being in the screen/window selection menu before the other person starts their stream. Works like a charm every time.</p>\n<p>The only thing we need now from Signal is simply not to disable the screen share button when someone else is starting a stream.</p>",
